The paper proposes a method for learning disentangled latent factors using a variational autoencoder and convolutional feature maps obtained from networks pretrained on the ImageNet database. This approach is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, given the focus on deep learning and image processing, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
